<td>
	<p>Welcome to my web page!</p>
	<p>I am <i>charg&eacute; de recherche</i> (<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Academic_ranks_in_France#Research-only_positions">researcher</a>) in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Theoretical_computer_science">theoretical computer science</a> at <a href="http://www.cnrs.fr">CNRS</a> (<a href="https://ins2i.cnrs.fr/">INS2I</a>).</p>
	
	<h4>Affiliation</h4>
	<ul>
		<li>
		<a href="https://ins2i.cnrs.fr/">CNRS</a>, <a href="http://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/index.php?lang=uk">LIPN</a>, <a href="https://www.univ-paris13.fr/">Universit&eacute; Paris 13</a>
		</li>
	</ul>
	
	<h4>Research interests</h4>
	<ul>
		<li>logical approaches to <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Structural_complexity_theory">structural complexity theory</a> (in particular <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Implicit_computational_complexity">implicit computational complexity</a>)</li>
		<li>foundational aspects of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Programming_language_theory">programming language theory</a> (<a href="http://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/lambda-calculus">lambda-calculi</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Process_calculus">concurrent process calculi</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Denotational_semantics">semantics</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Type_system">type systems</a>)</li>
		<li>More broadly: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logic_in_computer_science">logic in computer science</a>, <a href="http://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/linear+logic">linear logic</a>, <a href="https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/category+theory">category theory</a>
	</ul>

	<h4>Research-related activities and administration</h4>
	<ul>
		<li>Head of the <i>Types, models and programming theory</i> group within the <a href="https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/accueil/equipe/lcr/">Logic and Verification</a> team at LIPN</li>
		<li>Co-leader of the <a href="https://www.irif.fr/gt-scalp/index">Scalp</a> working group within the <a href="http://www.gdr-im.fr/">GDR Informatique Math&eacute;matique</a></li>
		<li>Member of the steering committee of <a href="http://fscdconference.org/">FSCD</a></li>
		<li>Member of the steering committee of SCOT (the successor of <a href="http://perso.ens-lyon.fr/patrick.baillot/DICE/">DICE</a>).
	</ul>

	<h4>Current/future events and ongoing projects</h4>
	<ul>
		<li>After the great success of the <a href="https://caleidoscope.sciencesconf.org/">first edition</a>, I am co-organizing the second edition of <i>Caleidoscope</i> (Complexity as a Kaleidoscope), a research school covering a great variety of different approaches to computational complexity. It is planned to take place at the <a href="https://universite.univ-paris-diderot.fr/structures/halle-aux-farines">Halle aux Farines</a> (<a href="https://u-paris.fr/en/">University of Paris</a>), the week of June 15th-19th, 2020. A web site will be available soon.</li>
		<li>The <a href="http://chocola.ens-lyon.fr/">Chocola seminar</a>.</li>
	</ul>
	
